Figs. 12 A, B, D
). Distinct longitudinal striae laterally on lamella. Rostral margin rounded, or with small medial indentation. Lamella 96–108 μm long; cusps 59 μm long. Lamellar cusps fused for third to half length, 32–46 μm, free portion of cusps contiguous anteromedially, leaving prodorsum visible through narrow long opening about 3 μm wide
